
<div class="hero-unit">
  <h1>Set up Password-less Logins</h1>
</div>

<div class="container">

  <div class="section">
  <div class="row">

    <form action="/auth" method="get" class="well span4">
      <label>Web Address:</label>
      <input type="text" name="me" class="span3" placeholder="yourdomain.com" />
      <p><button type="submit" class="btn">Sign In</button></p>
      <input type="hidden" name="redirect_uri" value="totp" />
    </form>

    <div class="span3">
      <h3>Install the Google Authenticator App</h3>
      <p>You can use the <a href="https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/1066447?hl=en">Google Authenticator app</a> as an authentication provider for your domain!</p>
      <p>Sign in with your domain to generate the QR code to set up the app.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="span3">
      <h3>Log in with your Pebble watch</h3>
      <p>You can use your Pebble watch to generate the 6-digit codes to sign in!</p>
      <p>You can read about how to <a href="http://aaronparecki.com/articles/2013/07/15/1/password-less-logins-via-indieauth-with-a-pebble-watch">set up your Pebble to sign in with IndieAuth</a>.</p>
    </div>

  </div><!-- row -->  
  </div><!-- section -->

</div><!-- container -->

